%S A220490 9,98,996,9996,99960,999960,9999780,99999360,999999360,9999999360,
%T A220490 99999951480,999999951480,9999999729720,99999693990000,
%U A220490 999999693990000,9999999693990000,99999999063360000,999999999063360000,9999999936135855360,99999999936135855360,999999798363798870960
%N A220490 The largest n-digit number whose last k digits are divisible by k for k = 1..n.
%C A220490 Does a(n) exist for all n? - _David A. Corneth_, Apr 22 2026
%H A220490 David A. Corneth, <a href="/A220490/a220490.gp.txt">PARI program</a>
%e A220490 There are ten one-digit numbers divisible by 1 and the largest is 9 so a(1)=9.
%e A220490 For two-digit numbers, the ones digit must make it divisible by 2, which gives 98 as the largest to satisfy the requirement. So a(2)=98.
%p A220490 f:= proc(n) local a, q, k,j;
%p A220490  if n >= 5 then q:= ilcm(10,n) elif n >= 2 then q:= ilcm(n,2) else q:= n fi;
%p A220490  if 10^n mod q = 0 then a:= 10^n - q else a:= floor(10^n/q)*q fi;
%p A220490  for k from a by -q do
%p A220490      if andmap(i -> (k mod 10^i) mod i = 0, [$2..n]) then return k fi
%p A220490    od
%p A220490 end proc:
%p A220490 map(f, [$1..17]); # _Robert Israel_, Apr 22 2026
